{
  "stem": "2170.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Ukrainians were always very nationalistic, and they wanted to get away from the communists.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because they couldn't, now they want to take their revenge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So Petliura was the name of the headquarters, and the yellow and blue flag-- Ukrainian-- the nationalistic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the police station, as I mentioned before, the chief commander, was-- his name was Baranchuk.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was an ex- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The next one was Dubina.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was another one who was in the Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they became the savages and the murderers of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When they used to come, and also into the factory-- especially Baranchuck-- to fix their uniforms and garments, he established a friendship with the people in the factory and with my brother-in-law.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the work was going on, but we had a feeling that something is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Not long time, as I mentioned before, the end of December, Ukrainian woman came from other towns in a town of Mogilev in the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they said they saw how the Jewish people were taken out from their homes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they had to dig their own graves, and they were shot into the graves.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Later on we heard, two weeks later, that in Kiev they took everybody out-- all the Jewish people-- out in the streets.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They told them they are going to be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They should take with them whatever they need.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they took them out of the city-- almost 80,000 or more.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And when they took them out from the city-- that's where the Ukrainian woman was telling us-- they took them to a place they called Babi Yar.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were all shot to death in that grave-- big, open grave in Babi Yar.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
